- cs.NE (Networks and Internet Architecture) is also likely as the problem arises in the context of analyzing network robustness.
- cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is relevant as the paper deals with finding the most vital edges in a graph.
- cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) is relevant as the paper deals with graph theory and optimization.
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is relevant as the paper provides refined computational tractability and hardness results.
